                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[3 Prime Video Shows You Should Watch This Weekend (October 10 - 12)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/prime-video-shows-to-watch-this-weekend-october-10/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/prime-video-logo-and-a-popcorn-bucket-next-to-it.png" length="3387" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Weekend]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This weekend, explore a nightmarish town, a time-bending pasture portal, and Tom Hardy like you've never seen him.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you’re looking for some good shows to binge this weekend that will indeed set the tone for your spooktacular month, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/offers?ref=dvm_us_dl_sl_go_br_brsa_mkw_p401-kw371-cr606-c&mrntrk=go_cmp-22386851402_adg-177983916460_ad-742438417875_aud-2358113831031%3Akwd-45697133742_dev-c_ext-&tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2017175&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fprime-video-shows-weekend-binge-september-26%2F&asc_campaign=Feed&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fprime-video-shows-to-watch-this-weekend-october-10%2F&asc_campaign=Feed" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Amazon Prime Video</a> has you covered. This weekend, we’re diving into a supernatural neo-Western starring Josh Brolin, a super creepy sci-fi horror series that’ll have you scratching your head, and a dark, provocative Tom Hardy series that’s making a comeback.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 06:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/prime-video-shows-to-watch-this-weekend-october-10/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[3 Netflix Shows You Need to Binge This Weekend (October 10 - 12)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/netflix-shows-weekend-binge-october-10/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Keeley]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/a-popcorn-bucket-and-the-netflix-logo-in-the-background.png" length="2279" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Netflix]]></category><category><![CDATA[Weekend]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Need a laugh? Want some zombie thrills? Fancy some superhero adventures? Dive in!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://www.netflix.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Netflix</a> has a wealth of TV shows at your fingertips—the tough part is deciding what to watch. If you've carved out some viewing time this weekend, I've got three recommendations for shows that are bound to entertain.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 10 Oct 2025 04:00:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/netflix-shows-weekend-binge-october-10/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Windows 11's New Start Menu Is Back]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/windows-11s-new-start-menu-is-back/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/windows-11-9.jpg" length="145007" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Will it actually roll out to everyone this time?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Microsoft is testing a revamped Start Menu for Windows 11, starting in the Canary Channel for Insiders. It’s much larger than the previous design, and it will <em>hopefully</em> require less scrolling or searching to find the apps you need.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 21:19:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/windows-11s-new-start-menu-is-back/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Home Assistant and iPhone Critical Alerts Are a Match Made in Heaven]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/home-assistant-iphone-critical-alerts/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Davidson]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/an-iphone-displaying-a-critical-alert-on-the-lock-screen.png" length="8979" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home Assistant]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[ios]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Never miss a notification again.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Some iPhone apps can use critical alerts to bypass your iPhone's settings and play audible notifications even when your iPhone is in Silent mode or Do Not Disturb focus. Using Home Assistant, it's possible to send bespoke critical alerts for any reason that you want.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 21:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/home-assistant-iphone-critical-alerts/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Intel’s Core Ultra Series 3 Processors Will Have a Few Surprises]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/intels-core-ultra-series-3-processors-will-have-a-few-surprises/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/the-intel-core-ultra-7-evo-edition-sticker-on-the-dell-14-premium-da14250-laptop.jpg" length="806" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[computer hardware]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Some good, some not so much.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>We're fast approaching the end of the year, and as it's usually the case, we're starting to see the stuff that will power our hardware next year. Intel's Core Ultra Series 3 is finally here, and there's a few things you should know.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 20:30:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/intels-core-ultra-series-3-processors-will-have-a-few-surprises/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This EcoFlow Power Station Could 'Overheat and Ignite' Without a Firmware Update]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-ecoflow-power-station-could-overheat-and-ignite-without-a-firmware-update/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ecoflow-portable-power-station-delta-max-2000.jpg" length="262" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Portable Power Station]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            If you have an EcoFlow Delta Max 2000 Power Station, install the latest firmware update now.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>EcoFlow has announced a recall of its Delta Max 2000 power stations, due to a problem that caused some units to “overheat and ignite.” You don’t have to return or mail the power station, though—you just need to install a firmware update.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 19:56:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-ecoflow-power-station-could-overheat-and-ignite-without-a-firmware-update/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Don't Overlook the Remote When Buying Your Next TV]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/dont-overlook-the-remote-when-buying-your-next-tv/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aran Folsom]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/05/person-s-finger-on-the-menu-button-on-a-universal-remote-control.jpg" length="235" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Minor oversights can have major repercussions.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The time has finally come to replace your old TV. You've checked every spec down to the <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/729890/what-is-peak-brightness/" target="_blank">nit count</a>, but have you thought about the remote? Is it missing essential features, or is it so feature-packed that you're left fumbling to find that one rarely-used yet super-important button? Is it compatible with the rest of your entertainment system? How easy will it be to replace if you don't want an aftermarket duplicate?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 18:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/dont-overlook-the-remote-when-buying-your-next-tv/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Here's How I Removed the Annoying Search Icons from My Windows 11 Taskbar]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/heres-how-i-removed-the-annoying-search-icons-from-my-windows-11-taskbar/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/52881834365_511de40661_o-1.jpg" length="293" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Keep only what you need on the taskbar.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The search bar on the Windows 11 taskbar allows you to quickly search for apps and files available on your device. If you're connected to the internet, you will also notice a small icon in the taskbar's search bar that changes every day. If you're like me and prefer the search bar to be free of any such icon, there are a few ways to disable it.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 18:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/heres-how-i-removed-the-annoying-search-icons-from-my-windows-11-taskbar/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Best October Amazon Prime Deals of 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/amazon-october-prime-day-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Kris Henges]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/amazon-logo-with-a-stack-of-shipping-boxes-in-front-set-against-an-orange-and-blue-background.png" length="1126" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Day 2025]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't wait!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Don't miss out on these last-minute deals!</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 17:28:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/amazon-october-prime-day-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Over-the-Air TV With DRM Might Need New Laws, Says FCC]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/over-the-air-tv-with-drm-might-need-new-laws-says-fcc/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/52815185161_ebcd114b9a_o.jpg" length="163191" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The legal future of ATSC 3.0 and NextGen TV is up in the air.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The FCC has just dropped a huge, 69-page draft ruling that directly tackles the fight against Digital Rights Management (DRM) on over-the-air television. Honestly, it's surprising that a draft rulemaking was released at all, considering the US government is currently shut down.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 17:24:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/over-the-air-tv-with-drm-might-need-new-laws-says-fcc/</guid></item></channel>
